<subSubSection id="C3556504FF86FFF0F392FC1B2AF070B0" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF0368FFF86FFF0F392FC1B2AF070B0" blockId="101.[151,1436,854,1167]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis id="B93BEA9DFF86FFF0F392FC1B2F4977C0" bold="true" box="[199,321,998,1023]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C4F4D0CFF86FFF0F212FC1B2C4177C1" authority="Fennah" authorityName="Fennah" authorityYear="1967" box="[327,585,998,1022]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pellax">
<emphasis id="B93BEA9DFF86FFF0F212FC1B2FF877C1" box="[327,496,998,1022]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Rhotana pellax</emphasis>
Fennah
</taxonomicName>
shows similarities to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4F4D0CFF86FFF0F06EFC1A2A3077C1" authority="Zelazny" authorityName="Zelazny" authorityYear="1981" box="[827,1080,998,1022]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B93BEA9DFF86FFF0F06EFC1A2DDF77C1" box="[827,983,999,1022]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">R. marmorata</emphasis>
Zelazny
</taxonomicName>
from South-East Asia. It can be separated from that species by orange markings on the head, pronotum and mesonotum, by the black forewing mark not reaching the hind margin at the tips of Ms1a and Ms1b, by the light infuscation on the remaining forewings being arranged in a different pattern, and by a sinuate process on the apical part of the male aedeagus. Both, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4F4D0CFF86FFF0F3C2FB8A2EF270B1" authorityName="Fennah" authorityYear="1967" box="[151,250,1142,1166]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pellax">
<emphasis id="B93BEA9DFF86FFF0F3C2FB8A2EF270B1" box="[151,250,1142,1166]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">R. pellax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4F4D0CFF86FFF0F264FB8A2FC670B1" authorityName="Zelazny" authorityYear="1981" box="[305,462,1143,1166]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B93BEA9DFF86FFF0F264FB8A2FC670B1" box="[305,462,1143,1166]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">R. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also show similarities to the species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C4F4D0CFF86FFF0F0E1FB8B2A5970B1" authorityName="Zelazny" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Bierman" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[948,1105,1142,1166]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pavo">
<emphasis id="B93BEA9DFF86FFF0F0E1FB8B2A5970B1" box="[948,1105,1142,1166]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Rhotana pavo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group.
</paragraph>
